We’ve got some new faces around here, so it’s time for a little ✨ get to know me ✨ post/ update☑️

Hi everyone! I’m Delaney Hogg Loomis and I’ve been a Realtor in the RVA area for just over a year now, WOW!

Time has flown by since I started in the business last November. With the support of my amazing husband, and many friends and family, + lots of coffee ☕️💕 I’ve had a wild ride of a year!

I’ve listed houses in Northumberland County, Henrico, Chesterfield, Glen Allen, ➕ more!

And I’ve helped my clients to buy in Henrico, Mechanicsville, Heathsville, + more!

I’m a coffee enthusiast, book lover, go-getter, and I absolutely love my job.✨

With my background being in Marketing (specifically fashion and sports), my 8+ years in the influencer sphere and sports marketing industries have prepared me SO much for this career path… I seriously think my younger self would be SHOCKED to see how much my experiences when I was 16 are translating into my career at 24..

I’ve always loved writing, photography, video work, and content strategy.. and now I get to use those in my career daily.☑️

I serve all of Virginia with Real Estate needs and I’m able to connect people from all over the country if they need it, which is super cool 😉🌎

When I’m not out showing houses or meeting with clients, you can find me at ERA Woody Hogg & Associates where I work full time as the Marketing and Events Manager.

Helping train agents, plan events, and whatever else they throw my way!🥳

And when I’m not there, you’ll find me with a cup of coffee, a book, and my cat, Summit, curled up next to me🤣📚

In our free time, you’ll find my husband, Ty, and I at our house doing renovations, at Lowe’s, picking stuff up for said renovations, or curled up on the couch watching CSI📺

We became home owners in September and were married in November.. so our free time is spent getting our house ready/ relaxing from getting our house ready.. I’ll update y’all when we have free time for anything outside of that 🤣

Thank you all for supporting me in this business this year. I can’t wait to see what 2023 has in store - and if you’re thinking about buying/selling, call or text me! 🤩

July Market Update 🐚✨🌊
➡️ now featuring Chesterfield County 😉

here’s the quick stats ☕️
➡️ average sales price is UP 
➡️ number of new listings /inventory is DOWN

And what I mean by down.. in Northumberland, we are seeing a difference from 7 new listings last July, to 4 new listings this July…

And on the larger scale of Chesterfield County, there were 580 new listings last July, and only 437 new listings this July..

That’s almost 150 new listings DOWN 🤯

Now what does that really mean? ⬇️

Whether we like it or not, there is still a housing shortage. Inventory is low. Supply is low. DEMAND is high!🏡

This means the market is still a sellers market in many areas. 

And whether you’re a buyer or seller, YOU NEED TO KNOW THIS!

Let’s grab a coffee and talk about how I can help you navigate this market, regardless of which side you’re on ☕️☑️

in 2023 (+ 2024) ➡️ we are GHOSTING what doesn’t serve us 👻❌

🖤 RENTING 
~ but why? Because even though interest rates have been ticking up slowly, 100% of your money going to someone else’s mortgage, has NOTHING on 6-8%🙅🏼‍♀️

🎃 SELF DOUBT
~ I will not lie to you, it was not easy buying our first house. My husband and I lost out on 7 houses before we found * the one * … and that one was still a massive fixer upper.

We had to make compromises, we had to save every penny, but it was SO worth it.

💀 FOR SALE BY OWNER 
~ if you’re a seller looking to sell your home on your own.. what’s your first step? You can get the photos and do the marketing sure.. but will you get top dollar? How do you feel about negotiating? What do you do with an inspection report?

Whether you’re thinking about listing or are currently listed FSBO, feel free to give me a call for a consult. 

And lastly, we are ghosting…

🦇 SETTLING

wait… I thought you just said you had to compromise…?

Well yes, but hear me out👀

We had to compromise on the condition of our home.

The houses we lost out on were essentially at the top of our budget, and we had NO wiggle room. We didn’t have more to put down, and the only thing we “had to give” at the time, was some sweat equity. 

When it comes to compromising, you need to list out your MUST HAVES. Do you need 3 bedrooms? A garage? What don’t you need? What can you give up? 

Find your wiggle room, and we will navigate from there 🥰🏡

Whether you’re looking to buy in 2023, or 2024, it’s never too early to sit down with me and get prepared. Let’s get coffee ☕️📲 804-551-1411

let this serve as a reminder that you can list your home at whichever time of year feels right for YOU🏡🥰

But why🧐

Ultimately, the time of year that is the best for you to sell is the best time of year to list. Period.

That being said, statistically, spring is when most people decide to list. Which means there is more options for buyers/ more competition.💪🏻🏡

While most people don’t like the move around the holidays, some people NEED to move around the holidays 🎅🏻✨🎄

That being said, schooling is also a factor. And while most families want to move over the summer, others may be comfortable with winter break (especially if they do year round schooling).

There are so many factors at play when selling your home; but having a realtor you TRUST to guide you through all those factors is 🔑

Why not ❌ FSBO ❌

Well if you’re looking for my honest opinion.. here it is.

I’m not saying it can’t be done, or it can’t be done well… but it can most definitely be done better

1st~ you get the listing photos taken, now what??

Are your photos “listing ready”… have you gone through room by room making recommendations and looking at the space with an unbiased eye?

Up next… distribution..

What sites will you be listed on and how do you get your home on them?

Not trying to toot my own horn but… 📯 TOOT TOOT

Our brokerage distributed to over 3,000 sites internationally.. just something to think about

Okay, let’s say you get your home listed, and you get it under contract.. NOW WHAT?

How do you negotiate? How do you do the paperwork? 

And seriously, stay with me… in what areas are you lacking?

Practice some self awareness, and ask yourself this question. Because it could make or break your transaction. 

Now some stats… 

FSBOs accounted for 10% of home sales in 2021. The typical FSBO home sold for $225,000 compared to $330,000 for agent-assisted home sales.

FSBO methods used to market home: 
Friends, relatives, or neighbors: 28%
Yard sign: 20%
Third party aggregator: 19%
Social networking websites: 17%
For-sale-by-owner website: 3%
Open house: 3%
Online classified ads: 3%
Multiple Listing Service (MLS) Website: 3%
Other website with real estate listings: 1%
Video hosting websites: 1%

Most difficult tasks for FSBO sellers: 
Preparing/fixing up home for sale: 6%
Getting the right price: 16%
Understanding and performing paperwork: 13%
Selling within the planned length of time: 10%
Having enough time to devote to all aspects of the sale: 1%
Attracting potential buyers: 1%
Helping buyers obtain financing: 1%

Source: 2022 National Association of REALTORS® Profile of Home Buyers and Sellers

I often get asked “Delaney, I’m thinking about selling in the next __ years… what can I be doing now to prepare?” 🧐🏡

That’s a GREAT QUESTION🥰✨ and one I love answering…

And the basics include updating your bathroom, kitchen, curb appeal, and appliances… but how are you supposed to do all of that while also remaining current?

How far in advance is too far in advance to start prepping? 🧐

My honest answer, I don’t think you can start prepping too soon. Your future self will thank you.

Last week, I went to a sellers house in Mechanicsville. They want to move to the beach in 2 years. They want to make updates. They want X number. They want to ✨ ENJOY ✨ these updates before their move.

So what did we do? I went over and did a full home evaluation. I told them everything that I think they could/ should do in the next two years to prepare. We made a room by room guide. Including inspiration photos and overall goal (WITH THEIR OVERALL TASTE).

And I had another client reach out who wants to move in 4 years.. so guess what? We are doing the 👏🏻 same 👏🏻 thing 👏🏻 but with the 4 year goal in mind.

The worst thing you can do for selling your house, is to allow yourself to getting to a place where you NEED TO SELL, and don’t have time to prep properly, therefore potentially earning less than what is possible.

I could go on about this forever, but if you’re curious about the numbers, want a second opinion, or need someone’s eye who happens to look at houses every day.. well, I’m your girl ☕️😉🏡

And for my first time home buyers, let me break down something that I think you’ll find helpful…

I met with a young couple yesterday for coffee, we talked about their timeline for buying and their lease is up in May. 

If they got preapproved right now, started looking on January 15th, did a 60 day closing timeline or less and closed on March 15th, their first mortgage payment would not be due until May 1st. 🏠🔑😍

This is a common misconception, you have your closing date where you pay your closing costs and down payment, but your first mortgage payment is usually not due for at least a month. 

maybe you’re hoping to save some money, but have no idea how much you might need to buy a home. This is something I would be happy to break down with you💵
